s music, and later in art and media, the author argues that 'Remix' punches above its deemed cultural weight.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAesthetics, Moderny20th century. 0aAppropriation (Art). 0aMashups (World Wide Web). 0aRemixes. 0aSampling (Sound). 4aArt. 4aCulture. 4aMusic. 4aNew Media. 4aPop. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z97831102385700 cprintz978399043499440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978399043500740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783990435007423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783990435007/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062112-9  DGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GAAc2000d2014